author: timesunion.com
title: Rodger's Quick Take
text: Give the Jets a tremendous amount of credit, but the Patriots still figured out a way to pull out a victory. If the Jets had a healthy Chris Ivory , the outcome might have been different because the Jets struggled running the ball. Once again, quarterback Tom Brady carried his team on his shoulders, and that's despite 11 drops from his receivers. Fortunately he has tight end Rob Gronkowski , and Gronk always comes through. Sunday against the Jets was no different. NewsChannel 13's Rodger Wyland can be heard weekdays from 9 a.m. to noon on WOFX 980 AM.
